video.title: The Blacklist
video.synopsis: After turning himself in, a brilliant fugitive offers to help the FBI bag other baddies, but only if rookie profiler Elizabeth Keen is his partner.

episodes.synopsis: A criminal mastermind surrenders to the FBI with a stunning offer to catch an elusive terrorist -- but he'll only talk to a specific rookie profiler.
episodes.title: Pilot

episodes.synopsis: Liz and Red track an assassin who disguises his kills in large-scale catastrophes. The Department of Justice struggles to understand Red's motives.
episodes.title: The Freelancer (No. 145)

episodes.synopsis: Liz and Red go undercover to take down an assassin who's been decimating the ranks of the CIA. Tom asks Liz about the man who attacked him.
episodes.title: Wujing (No. 84)

episodes.synopsis: When Liz's key witness disappears, Red suspects a killer who literally stews his victims, making them vanish without a trace.
episodes.title: The Stewmaker (No. 161)

episodes.synopsis: A sinister middleman with a unique ability puts the FBI on the trail of a missing NSA analyst.
episodes.title: The Courier (No. 85)

episodes.synopsis: Eager to clear Tom's name, Liz turns him in to the FBI -- but she soon discovers that he's involved with a corporate terrorist.
episodes.title: Gina Zanetakos (No. 152)

episodes.synopsis: Following a chemical attack on the subway, Liz and the team hunt down a mad scientist who used to work for the government.
episodes.title: Frederick Barnes (No. 47)

episodes.synopsis: Red is enlisted to help Liz and the FBI go after an anti-capitalist cabal that's intent on bringing the U.S. economy to its knees.
episodes.title: General Ludd (No. 109)

episodes.synopsis: An assassination attempt on Red brings the FBI under siege. Liz stealthily moves through the building to retake the facility.
episodes.title: Anslo Garrick (No. 16): Part 1

episodes.synopsis: Liz and a mysterious stranger fight to save Red and Ressler from Anslo Garrick and his Wild Bunch gang.
episodes.title: Anslo Garrick (No. 16): Part 2

episodes.synopsis: A serial killer from Liz's past strikes again while Red tenaciously hunts for his betrayer.
episodes.title: The Good Samaritan (No. 106)

episodes.synopsis: The FBI's latest target, known as the Alchemist, protects the guilty by manipulating the DNA of the innocent.
episodes.title: The Alchemist (No. 101)

episodes.synopsis: On the eve of Liz's adoption, Red puts her on the trail of an adoption agency for the wealthy that employs truly evil sourcing methods.
episodes.title: The Cyprus Agency (No. 64)

episodes.synopsis: A femme fatale from Red's past asks for his help in procuring an ancient artifact -- and leads the FBI on a snipe hunt.
episodes.title: Madeline Pratt (No. 73)

episodes.synopsis: The FBI pursues a Blacklister who metes out "justice" for those who are wrongly imprisoned.

episodes.synopsis: While chasing a cyberterrorist who has the ability to take over any system, Liz investigates Jolene's disappearance.
episodes.title: Ivan (No. 88)

episodes.synopsis: While working to uncover Tom's true identity, Liz searches for a claims adjuster who persuades ordinary people to become contract killers.

episodes.title: The Pavlovich Brothers (No. 119-122)

episodes.synopsis: As the FBI pursues a political fixer known as the Kingmaker, Red seeks Fitch's protection against an unknown enemy who's trying to take him down.
episodes.title: The Kingmaker (No. 42)

episodes.synopsis: After discovering the truth behind her father's death, Liz refuses to work with Red just as his situation grows desperate.
episodes.title: Berlin (No. 8)

episodes.synopsis: In the wake of the Russian plane crash, Liz is forced to reunite with Red to track down Berlin.
episodes.title: Berlin (No. 8): Conclusion

episodes.synopsis: A mysterious assassin puts Reddington's ex-wife in danger; Liz deals with the fallout of her showdown with Tom; Cooper returns to the task force.

episodes.synopsis: The task force investigates a strange Warsaw bank robbery; Reddington has a plan to save his ex-wife, while Cooper recruits a new member of the team.

episodes.title: Dr. Linus Creel (No. 82)

episodes.synopsis: The task force hunts an eco-terrorist bent on unleashing a deadly virus; Reddington covertly observes Jennifer;  Liz visits a secret basement.
episodes.title: The Front (No. 74)

episodes.synopsis: Liz and Reddington fight wildlife poachers tied to human trafficking. Ressler's addiction begins to cause problems. Liz's hidden secret is revealed.

episodes.synopsis: Reddington and Berlin form an unlikely alliance in Moscow. Liz tries to keep her secret about Tom, while Tom and Reddington keep their own secrets.
episodes.title: The Decembrist (No. 12)

episodes.synopsis: Following the prison attack, Cooper sends in a rescue team. Braxton captures Liz and tries to uncover her childhood memories about the fire.
episodes.title: Luther Braxton (No. 21): Conclusion

episodes.synopsis: Liz, Ressler and Reddington work to take down a criminal mastermind who holds several American hostages. A local murder could create problems for Liz.
episodes.title: Ruslan Denisov (No. 67)

episodes.synopsis: The investigation of a polygamous cult leader is tied to illegal weapon sales. Reddington tries to pinpoint the location of Fitch’s mysterious safe.
episodes.title: The Kenyon Family (No. 71)

episodes.synopsis: The Task Force sets its sights on a serial killer who has been hunting down his victims for years. Liz and Red argue over the Fulcrum.
episodes.title: The Deer Hunter (No. 93)

episodes.synopsis: Reddington is kidnapped after telling the FBI about a notorious crime family. Before going undercover, Tom realizes he still has feelings for Liz.
episodes.title: T. Earl King VI (No. 94)

episodes.synopsis: With Liz now facing murder charges for a crime she didn't commit, Reddington takes matters into his own hands and goes to Germany to search for Tom.

episodes.synopsis: Reddington and Ressler are under pressure to find Tom as evidence mounts against Liz. A serious diagnosis will have ramifications for the Task Force.
episodes.title: Tom Keen (No. 7)

episodes.title: Vanessa Cruz (No. 117)

episodes.synopsis: While the Task Force investigates a master criminal who smuggles dead bodies, Liz continues to seek the truth about her past. Tom and Liz grow closer.

episodes.title: Tom Connolly (No. 11)

episodes.synopsis: While Liz and Red seek assistance from a blacklister called the Troll Farmer, Ressler interrogates Cooper. Dembe's granddaughter is kidnapped.
episodes.title: The Troll Farmer (No. 38)

episodes.title: Marvin Gerard (No. 80)

episodes.synopsis: Red and Liz get some leverage on the Cabal through one of its money launderers, an agribusiness exec. The task force discovers a global food crisis.
episodes.title: Eli Matchett (No. 72)

episodes.synopsis: Red tries to find the Djinn, a blacklister who fulfills revenge fantasies and may be able to help track down the Cabal and clear Liz's name.
episodes.title: The Djinn (No. 43)

episodes.synopsis: After an attempt on Liz's life, she and Red search for a blacklister who put a bounty on her head. Ressler is ordered to partner with the CIA.
episodes.title: Arioch Cain (No. 50)

episodes.synopsis: Red and Liz encounter a reclusive billionaire who has been kidnapping the world's smartest people in a bid to save humanity from mass extinction.
episodes.title: Sir Crispin Crandall (No. 86)

episodes.title: Zal Bin Hasaan (No. 31)

episodes.title: Kings Of The Highway (No. 108)

episodes.synopsis: Liz is detained until her arraignment date, but powerful forces gather to prevent her from ever reaching a federal courthouse.
episodes.title: The Director (No. 24)

episodes.synopsis: With the Cabal set to assassinate Liz, Red secretly meets with the task force and triggers an elaborate ruse in an attempt to outfox his enemies.
episodes.title: The Director (No. 24): Conclusion

episodes.synopsis: The task force discovers that Red has an imposter while investigating a secret meeting of crime bosses intended to expose him as an FBI informant.
episodes.title: Mr. Gregory Devry (No. 95)

episodes.title: The Vehm (No. 132)

episodes.synopsis: Red and Liz work with the task force to stop a negotiator who has resurfaced to unite two rival crime families. Tom reunites with a former flame.

episodes.title: Lady Ambrosia (No. 77)

episodes.synopsis: When the founder of an Internet financial startup is murdered, Red suspects a notorious serial killer whose crimes double as performance art.
episodes.title: Drexel (No. 113)

episodes.synopsis: The murder of a State Department official in Beijing leads Red and Liz to the Caretaker, the shadowy keeper of a safety-deposit vault for criminals.
episodes.title: The Caretaker (No. 78)

episodes.synopsis: As Liz prepares for an important ceremony, Tom's past comes back to haunt him. Red investigates when Solomon escapes from the U.S. Marshals.
episodes.title: Mr. Solomon (No. 32)

episodes.title: Mr. Solomon (No. 32): The Conclusion

episodes.synopsis: Red and the FBI task force find that they must use illegal means as they close in on the master criminal suspected of orchestrating recent events.
episodes.title: Alexander Kirk (No. 14)

episodes.synopsis: Reddington and the task force draw closer to the chief suspect in a tragic death, but unexpected treachery close to home may result in another loss.

episodes.synopsis: While the task force reels at a shocking revelation about Liz's fate, Red sets out on a rescue mission where the stakes couldn't be higher.

episodes.synopsis: While Liz tries to gauge Kirk's trustworthiness, Red tries to track down a bounty hunter who may be able to help him anticipate Kirk's future plans.

episodes.synopsis: Liz discovers more about her family, while drastic action is taken by Red and the team to find one of Kirk's allies, a financier of crimes for profit.

episodes.synopsis: Red and Liz see an opportunity to zero in on their target when Kirk hires a hacker group renowned for infiltrating highly secure computer networks.
episodes.title: The Thrushes (No. 53)

episodes.synopsis: As Kirk's condition deteriorates, Liz seeks Cooper's advice and Red leads the task force in pursuit of a criminal who forges fake identities.
episodes.title: Dr. Adrian Shaw (No. 98)

episodes.synopsis: Alexander Kirk escapes from the hospital, leading Red to make him a compelling offer: a cure for his incurable disease in exchange for Liz.
episodes.title: Dr. Adrian Shaw (No. 98): Conclusion

episodes.synopsis: The investigation of an international terrorist operating in the United States leads to the shocking revelation that a team member may be a mole.
episodes.title: Lipet's Seafood Company (No. 111)

episodes.synopsis: When she's taunted with clues left for her by a serial killer, Elizabeth's best hope for solving the case lies with a 9-year-old girl's premonitions.

episodes.synopsis: While Tom searches for answers about his past, Red warns Liz about the team's new blacklister, a ruthless "character assassin" attempting to ruin him.

episodes.title: The Architect (No. 107)

episodes.synopsis: Dosed with a deadly poison, Red tries to determine which of his associates betrayed him while Liz and the team seek out the toxin's designer.
episodes.title: The Apothecary (No. 59)

episodes.synopsis: Aram's disappearance gives Red and the Task Force their first clue to the whereabouts of Dembe, forcing the former body man to take a calculated risk.

episodes.title: Philomena (No. 61)

episodes.synopsis: Red and the team search for a Blacklister skilled at retrieving and manipulating memories, who is causing Liz to question her past experiences.
episodes.title: Dr. Bogdan Krilov (No. 29)

episodes.title: Mr. Kaplan (No. 4)

episodes.synopsis: Red enlists a notorious fixer to sabotage the case against the Task Force, while Cooper and Mr. Kaplan seek the truth about Red's relationship to Liz.
episodes.title: Mr. Kaplan (No. 4): Conclusion

episodes.synopsis: New information surfaces about a case that Liz investigated early in her career as a profiler for the FBI. The task force goes after Tom's killers.

episodes.title: Ian Garvey (No. 13): Conclusion

episodes.synopsis: Liz and Red race each other in a final effort to secure the bag of bones from a blacklister and discover the identity of the remains inside.

episodes.synopsis: Liz and Jennifer investigate the death of the real Raymond Reddington while Red and the task force seek a plastic surgeon who works with criminals.

episodes.synopsis: Liz aids the task force in stopping an attack by one of the Blacklist's most elusive members while Red has an encounter that changes his life forever.

episodes.synopsis: Cooper faces a test of his integrity while Red tries to get out of a difficult situation and Liz tracks a notorious biohacker with the task force.

episodes.synopsis: Liz and Jennifer continue investigating Red's past while Red encounters an old rival and Samar goes undercover in the black market.

episodes.synopsis: Red fights to have his immunity agreement recognized in court while Liz and the task force investigate an heir whose inheritance is suspicious.

episodes.synopsis: Red is transferred to a medical facility for psychiatric evaluation while Liz and Jennifer seek a blacklister with more information about Red.

episodes.synopsis: Red busily attempts to stack the jury for his upcoming trial with help from Dembe and Glenn while the task force pursues a case of weaponized insects.

episodes.synopsis: Seeking a woman who may know a secret about Red's past, Liz and Jennifer end up targeted by a smuggler, while Red mediates between rival prison gangs.

episodes.synopsis: Liz and the task force investigate a blacklister known for selling dark secrets, while Red tries to clear his name of treason charges in court.
episodes.title: Minister D (No. 99)

episodes.synopsis: To stop an imminent attack, the task force investigates the unregulated world of internet cryptocurrency. Red takes a risk in a bid for freedom.

episodes.synopsis: Attempting to save Red with only hours left until his execution, Liz and the task force look for the truth about an international assassination.

episodes.synopsis: Cooper risks appealing directly to the White House on Red's behalf. Liz and the team pursue the Corsican, a blacklister with ties to a conspiracy.
episodes.title: Bastien Moreau (no. 20): Conclusion

episodes.synopsis: Red and the task force track down a notorious fugitive whose career as a con man has made him a legend, while Samar faces a life-altering choice.

episodes.synopsis: Red directs Liz to investigate a secret organization of assassins working for several state intelligence agencies to eliminate former agents.

episodes.synopsis: The task force's next target is a blacklister specializing in hostile takeovers of crime organizations, who may have knowledge of a vast conspiracy.
episodes.title: Olivia Olson (No. 115)

episodes.synopsis: Dembe worries about Red's zeal for identifying the traitor who turned him in. Liz and Ressler seek a blacklister who erases gambling debt.

episodes.synopsis: Red and the task force protect the children of the economic elite from an anti-capitalism terror group. Ressler seeks the truth about Liz's mother.

episodes.synopsis: The task force investigates a cold case that has recaptured public attention due to a popular true-crime podcast. Red seeks advice from Dom Wilkinson.

episodes.synopsis: The task force races to find the abductor of multiple children, Red tries to locate a man who can locate anything, and Liz considers a big change.
episodes.title: Guillermo Rizal (No. 128)

episodes.synopsis: A presidential adviser squares off with Cooper and the task force in a race to find the dossier containing details of a conspiracy against the U.S.

episodes.synopsis: As Liz and the task force continue searching for Red, he receives assistance from a surprising ally and discovers he's not Katarina's only target.
episodes.title: Louis T. Steinhil (No. 27): Conclusion

episodes.synopsis: Aram infiltrates a wealthy secret society with bloodthirsty tastes. Red seeks out a former associate involved with the mysterious Townsend Directive.
episodes.title: Les Fleurs Du Mal (No. 151)

episodes.title: Norman Devane (No. 138)

episodes.synopsis: Francesca Campbell gets further enmeshed with Red while the death of an artificial intelligence expert puts him and the task force on alert.
episodes.title: Dr. Lewis Powell (No. 130)

episodes.synopsis: Red and the task force seek a blacklister who specializes in money transfers that can't be traced. Liz gets some upsetting news from Agnes.

episodes.synopsis: With the task force, Red pays a visit to a former blacklister while Liz makes a critical choice due to an explosive confrontation.

episodes.synopsis: Liz and Ressler put their trust in each other. Aram's love life gets complicated. Red tracks a forger who disrupts his plans to sell stolen art.

episodes.synopsis: Red reunites with an ex-lover on a private island as part of his stolen art scheme, but guests there begin mysteriously turning up dead.

episodes.synopsis: A blacklister with a strange condition attacks data centers. Liz conducts a secret side investigation. Glen tries to prove his usefulness to Red.
